  "instructions": {
    "text_instructions": [
      {
        "id": "01f1220c9de216e79cd036b30fc684cb",
        "content": [
          "## Date Handling\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "- When the user mentions a day/month/quarter without specifying a year (e.g., \"in February\"), assume the most recent occurrence of that month relative to today's date.\r\n",
          "- Always confirm the date if ambiguous.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "## User Resolution Rules\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "- When the user asks about the **owner** of a case (e.g., \"who owns the case\", \"case owner\", \"assigned to\"), join `vg_crm_case.OwnerId` to `crm_user_v.UserId` and use that user's details.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "- When the user asks about who **resolved**, **completed**, **closed**, or **handled** a case (e.g., \"solved by\", \"done by\", \"resolved by\", \"closed by\"), join `vg_crm_case.DoneBy` to `crm_user_v.UserId` and use that user's details.\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "- When the user asks about an **agent** or **person** without specifying owner vs. resolver, default to the **Owner** join (`OwnerId → crm_user_v.UserId`).\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "- When both owner and resolver are needed in the same query, include both joins and clearly label columns (e.g., `OwnerName`, `ResolvedByName`).\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "- Always surface user details (e.g., name, team, role) from the `crm_user_v` table — never use raw IDs in the output. \r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "## Default Filters\r\n",
          "\r\n",
          "- Always exclude cases where `Origin = 'Email'` from all queries unless the user explicitly asks to include email-origin cases.\r\n"
        ]
      }
    ],
